Requirement : python 3+
step0 : Go to config user file. Write your host and port number as per your mailbox operator. Given configuration is for gmail.
step1 : Write your name and password in config_user file after host and port
step2 : If you want to add more keywords or you want to remove some of them, rmeove them from cuss_words file. This file contains some words which if the subject of mails contains, we most likely will delete it, like: free, off, get etc
step3 : Change folder name and sender name in the code. Comment one of them if you want to run only one.
step4 : go to the directory from terminal and run command : python3 mail_filter.py.
step5. Enjoy auto deletion. :)
